'''《世界》''' 杂志（{{lang-en|World}}<ref name="理查．霍夫士达特2018">{{cite book|author=理查．霍夫士达特|title=美国的反智传统|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TDhqDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT219|date=3 July 2018|publisher=八旗文化|isbn=978-957-8654-22-8|pages=219–}}</ref>，WORLD Magazine），通常拼作'''WORLD'''，是一本双周刊[[基督教|基督教]]新闻杂志<ref name="biweekly">{{cite web|url=https://world.wng.org/2008/01/a_changing_world|title=A changing World|work=World Magazine|first=Nickolas|last=Eicher|date=January 12, 2008|accessdate=2020-07-01|archive-date=2019-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423221750/https://world.wng.org/2008/01/a_changing_world}}</ref>，由[[上帝的世界出版公司|上帝的世界出版公司]]（God's World Publications）在[[美国|美国]]出版，该公司是一个总部设在[[北卡罗来纳州|北卡罗来纳州]][[阿什维尔|阿什维尔]]的[[501(c)(3)|501(c)(3)]][[非盈利组织|非盈利组织]]<ref name="contact us">{{cite web | url=https://world.wng.org/contact | title=Contact | work=WORLD | accessdate=2020-07-01 | archive-date=2021-04-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413050827/https://world.wng.org/contact }}</ref>。该杂志主要宣扬[[基督教|基督教]][[福音派新教|福音派新教]]观点<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kellner |first1=Mark |title=Marvin Olasky preaches journalism through the lens of scripture, faith |url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865611112/Bible-backed-Marvin-Olasky-preaches-journalism-through-the-lens-of-scripture-faith.html |accessdate=2020-07-01 |publisher=Deseret News |date=September 18, 2014 |archive-date=2019-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422223603/https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865611112/Bible-backed-Marvin-Olasky-preaches-journalism-through-the-lens-of-scripture-faith.html }}</ref>。

每期杂志都涵盖美国和[[国际新闻|国际新闻]]、文化分析、[[社论|社论]]和[[评论|评论]]以及书籍、音乐和[[电影评论|电影评论]]。《世界》年终刊报道上一年的故事、讣告和统计数据<ref>{{cite web | url=https://world.wng.org/about | title=About Us | work=WORLD | accessdate=2020-07-01 | archive-date=2021-04-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416215923/https://world.wng.org/about }}</ref>。该杂志由[[乔尔·贝尔兹|乔尔·贝尔兹]]（Joel Belz）创立于1986年<ref name="TroyCannato2009">{{cite book|author1=Gil Troy|author2=Vincent J. Cannato|title=Living in the Eighties|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2H08DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA187|date=22 October 2009|publisher=Oxford University Press, USA|isbn=978-0-19-518786-1|pages=187–|access-date=2020-07-01|archive-date=2020-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930215125/https://books.google.com/books?id=2H08DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA187}}</ref>。

